    "parameters": [],
    "return_type": "",
    "exceptions": [],
    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "A one-character string used by the writer to escape characters that require escaping: the delimiter, the quotechar, '\\r', '\\n' and any of the characters in lineterminator are escaped if quoting is set to QUOTE_NONE; the quotechar is escaped if doublequote is False; the escapechar itself. On reading, the escapechar removes any special meaning from the following character. It defaults to None, which disables escaping. Changed in version 3.11: An empty escapechar is not allowed."
    },
